  "prompt": "I'm going to a wedding that my boyfriend is in, I'm a +1. I feel really nervous and anxious about meeting people in his life, is this normal?",
  "response": "Yes, it's completely normal to feel nervous and anxious in this situation! Being a +1 at a wedding where your boyfriend is involved can feel overwhelming, especially if you're meeting important people in his life for the first time. Here\u2019s why it\u2019s normal and how you can approach it:\n\n### Why It\u2019s Normal:\n1. **New Social Environment:** You\u2019ll be surrounded by people you don\u2019t know, and it\u2019s natural to feel uneasy in unfamiliar settings.\n2. **Desire to Make a Good Impression:** You likely want to leave a positive impression on your boyfriend\u2019s friends and family, which can add pressure.\n3. **Focus on Your Boyfriend:** Since he\u2019s in the wedding, he may be busy with responsibilities, leaving you to navigate conversations on your own.\n4. **Weddings Are Emotional:** Weddings can stir up a range of emotions, which might amplify your anxiety.\n\n### Tips to Feel More Comfortable:\n1. **Talk to Your Boyfriend:** Let him know how you\u2019re feeling. He can introduce you to people, give you some background on key guests, and check in with you throughout the event.\n2. **Prepare Conversation Starters:** Think of a few simple questions or topics (e.g., \"How do you know the couple?\" or \"What\u2019s your favorite thing about weddings?\") to make small talk easier.\n3. **Focus on the Purpose:** Remember, everyone is there to celebrate the couple. You don\u2019t need to be the center of attention\u2014just be kind and present.\n4. **Take Breaks:** If you feel overwhelmed, step outside or find a quiet space to recharge.\n5. **Dress Confidently:** Wear something that makes you feel comfortable and confident. When you feel good in what you\u2019re wearing, it can help ease some anxiety.\n6. **Remind Yourself It\u2019s Temporary:** The wedding is just one day, and most people will be focused on the couple, not on judging you.\n7. **Bring a Backup Plan:** If you\u2019re really nervous, consider bringing a close friend or family member if it\u2019s appropriate and the couple is okay with it.\n\n### Final Thought:\nIt\u2019s a sign that you care about your boyfriend and the people in his life that you\u2019re feeling this way. Most people will likely be friendly and welcoming, and chances are, you\u2019ll have a great time once you settle in. Take a deep breath, be yourself, and enjoy the celebration!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
